reviewerName: I'd rather be at the Beach
reviewText: Uncle Buck is a classic movie in this family!  John Candy was born to play Uncle Buck with a cast of youngsters that were awesome in their roles, too.  The children's parents have to leave suddenly when the mother's father is taken very ill.  The only person they can get to watch the kids is the bachelor uncle, Uncle Buck, who is childless and known to be undependable.  They are not too happy about leaving the 3 children with him, but there is no choice.  Some great hilarious situations arise from this and I won't spoil them here.  Surprisingly, this is a multi-layered story that manages to always keep your attention.  Lots of surprises and LOTS OF FUN!

reviewText: Ahhh, the great outdoors...so peaceful....not! What a hilarious movie! John Candy and Dan Akroyd vacation with their families in a cabin in the woods. Humor depicts how families can be complicated while bears, racoons and bats liven up their peaceful getaway. They say lightning doesn't strike the same place twice, but how about sssssssixxxxxtty ssssssiixxxx times! Uncle Buck is another good movie with John Candy.
